They are out of tune, very much.

01:04.037 --> 01:07.244
Do it properly. Now.

01:28.812 --> 01:32.218
Come along. Let’s have it again.

01:38.929 --> 01:42.086
Must say in tune, in proper tune,
you see?

01:42.111 --> 01:46.976
Just without tune if you go out…
you play and then they should sing.

01:54.491 --> 01:58.850
Where are they? Those who
are singing?

01:58.875 --> 02:02.491
They should be there, you see, that’s
why, they are not in tune with you.

02:02.516 --> 02:07.955
Come here, those who are singing.
That’s better, that’s the reason.

02:12.870 --> 02:16.627
You must sit with the musicians
and sing in tune, alright?

02:16.652 --> 02:18.944
Not without tune.

02:20.410 --> 02:23.680
Thus vibrations won’t come.

02:26.674 --> 02:31.188
Vibrations are not flowing.
Is better to sing…

02:31.802 --> 02:36.489
not in tune, better sing like that.

02:37.366 --> 02:41.054
They don’t know how to sing it.

02:51.964 --> 02:54.550
Who has fixed this?

02:58.396 --> 03:01.863
Catching on the Sahasrara.

03:11.250 --> 03:14.365
Make it in Indian tune.

03:31.665 --> 03:35.548
So that’s a very not proper way.
Let her sing,

03:35.573 --> 03:38.358
she knows. Let her sing,
she’ll tell you.

03:38.383 --> 03:41.178
You see, the vibrations could not
My Sahasrara’s caught up.

03:41.203 --> 03:44.440
Sit down, all of you sit down.

03:49.680 --> 03:53.205
These are mantras, this is not song,
is mantras, you see?

03:53.230 --> 03:58.151
Are to be said with deliberations
and understanding.

07:28.951 --> 07:32.661
You see, how it should be sung,
not that like

07:32.686 --> 07:36.321
a tiger is running after you.

07:36.346 --> 07:39.763
It's a deliberate thing, is mantras,
you see?

07:39.788 --> 07:43.047
Everybody has no right to sing
mantras also.

07:43.072 --> 07:46.405
You must sing with deliberations.

07:47.456 --> 07:49.000
Now let us hear how they sing,

07:49.025 --> 07:51.385
as I don’t want to catch again
My Sahasrara.

07:51.410 --> 07:55.118
Now which one, what one is
they were singing?

07:55.709 --> 07:58.279
What is the one they were singing?

07:58.304 --> 08:04.042
Yogi: The 10 names of Shri Lakshmi.
Shri Mataji: Ah?

08:04.067 --> 08:11.262
Yogi: The 10 names of Shri Lakshmi.
Or nine…

08:11.790 --> 08:16.699
Now. Do it slowly, steadily and without
hurrying up.

08:16.724 --> 08:20.194
And understanding what
you are saying.

08:20.219 --> 08:27.536
She rides on an elephant,
not in an aeroplane.

08:28.802 --> 08:33.672
Sahaja yogi: Shri Mataji, shall we
sing it in one part or we can

08:33.697 --> 08:36.771
try to sing it in two parts?
Shri Mataji: No, one part.

08:36.796 --> 08:39.586
Two parts is not good. That also
is wrong. One part.

08:39.611 --> 08:42.447
One part and with deliberations,
see?

08:42.472 --> 08:45.235
Every word should be clear cut.

08:45.260 --> 08:52.785
Then it is a mantras, you see? These
are the words which are enlightened,

08:55.310 --> 08:59.112
and this is only very few people
have this Adhikara,

08:59.137 --> 09:04.745
